'''Tschüss''' is an informal [[German language|German]] farewell, used in much the same way as "good-bye" in [[English language|English]]-speaking countries such as the [[United States]] or [[Great Britain]]. It is derived from the [[Low German]] language (see also [[Moin]]), and has historically been more common in northern [[Germany]], though it has gained country-wide acceptance. However, in southern [[Germany]] it is more common for the informal farewell [[ciao]] or [[adieu]] to be used, and the farewell [[Auf Wiedersehen]] is considered more formal.

